<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-X-SIDE17-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Here's some background on the ``X-Files'' players
 &HT;    By Kevin D. Thompson
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   So, you're going to see ``The X-Files: Fight the Future.''
There's only one problem. You've never seen ``The X-Files.'' Don't
sweat it. Here's a handy guide to all the key players:
</P>
<P>
   FOX MULDER
</P>
<P>
   (David Duchovny)
</P>
<P>
   This Oxford graduate was on the FBI fast-track until he started
chasing aliens and paranormal phenomena. Until recently, he was
steadfastly convinced that extraterrestrials existed. Now he's not
so sure what the truth is. Sometimes referred to as ``Spooky''
Mulder.
</P>
<P>
   DANA SCULLY
</P>
<P>
   (Gillian Anderson)
</P>
<P>
   Was paired with Mulder to debunk his ``the truth is out there''
theories. A no-nonsense medical doctor who once believed there was
a scientific explanation behind every X-file. Now she knows there
isn't.
</P>
<P>
   WALTER SKINNER
</P>
<P>
   (Mitch Pileggi)
</P>
<P>
   The FBI's hunky assistant director. Is often at odds over
Mulder's unorthodox methods. Although Skinner cares about his best
agents, it's never explained where he gets his orders. Looks good
in briefs.
</P>
<P>
   CIGARETTE-SMOKING MAN
</P>
<P>
   (William B. Davis)
</P>
<P>
   A chain-smoking devil who once sinisterly bragged, ``I've seen
presidents die.'' Works for a shadowy international organization
and could be Mulder's father.
</P>
<P>
   THE LONE GUNMEN
</P>
<P>
   Three geeky-looking guys Mulder often goes to for help. There's
the long-haired Langly (Dean Haglund), the combat boot-wearing
Frohike (Tom Braidwood) and the bearded systems expert Byers (Bruce
Harwood).
</P>
<P>
   WELL-MANICURED MAN
</P>
<P>
   (John Neville)
</P>
<P>
   The one man who can intimidate Cigarette Smoking Man. Always
nattily dressed, Well-Manicured Man is often seen barking icy
orders to his syndicate underlings in a smoke-filled room.
</P>
<P>
   SAMANTHA MULDER
</P>
<P>
   (Megan Leitch)
</P>
<P>
   Mulder's sister, who may or may not have been kidnapped by
aliens when she was 8 years old. Might be Cigarette Smoking Man's
daughter.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
