   SCIENCE/MEDICINE (a and/or l category)
</P>
<P>
   SALAMANDER-LAWSUIT _ AUSTIN _ Back in 1946, when biologists
first scooped up and identified what would become known as the
Barton Springs salamander, they couldn't have known the huge role
their discovery would come to have on the local scene or the
potential havoc that two other amphibian enthusiasts would visit on
Austin 52 years later in defense of the salamander. The salamander,
with considerable help from Alan Hamilton and Robert Barnhart and a
ruling from a federal judge, could cause the closure of all or most
of Barton Springs for the summer, just as temperatures are soaring
over the century mark. (Wear, Austin American-Statesman) MOVED.
</P>
