A1086 &Cx1f; tic-z
r s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-FBN-CARDS-NOTEBOOK-AZ     06-16 0687
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBN-CARDS-NOTEBOOK-AZR </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
CARDINALS ADD MORE TIGHT ENDS TO ROSTER 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By STEVE SCHOENFELD  
 c.1998 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   TEMPE, ARIZ. - Tight end suddenly has become a crowded position
for the Cardinals.
</P>
<P>
   Fifth-round draft pick  &UR; Terry Hardy signed a one-year deal
Monday, the same day former Cardinal  &UR; Jarius Hayes, who had been
playing in the NFL Europe League, returned to the team.
</P>
<P>
   The signings of Hardy and Hayes give the Cardinals five tight
ends going into next month's training camp. They join veterans
 &UR; Chris Gedney and
 &UR; Johnny McWilliams and rookie  &UR; Eli Workman, an undrafted free agent
from Colorado State.
</P>
<P>
   The Cardinals are expected to have three tight ends on their
active roster at the start of the regular season, with Gedney and
McWilliams expected to fill two of the spots.
</P>
<P>
   ``I think it's wide open, all the way,'' tight ends coach  &UR; Hank
Kuhlmann said. &QL; 
Hardy is the fifth draft pick to sign, joining fourth-round
choice &UR; Michael Pittman, Fresno State running back; sixth-round pick
 &UR; Zack Walz, Dartmouth linebacker; and seventh-round picks  &UR; Jomo
Cousins, Florida A&AMP;M defensive end, and  &UR; Ron Janes, Missouri
fullback. &QL; 
No longer a spectator
</P>
<P>
   Hardy, who played at Southern Mississippi, participated in his
first rookie camp workout Monday and then acknowledged he will have
to have surgery on his injured left shoulder after the season.
</P>
<P>
   ``After the season, I plan on having it operated on, but I'm not
worried about playing on it because I've done it,'' said Hardy, who
first injured the shoulder against Florida State two years ago.
</P>
<P>
   Team officials wouldn't let Hardy practice last week while he
was unsigned because of the risk of him reinjuring his shoulder.
</P>
<P>
   Cardinals doctors discovered Hardy had a slightly torn rotator
cuff when he had a physical examination at last month's minicamp.
</P>
<P>
   ``He's healthy enough to practice,'' Coach  &UR; Vince Tobin said.
``Whether he has a chance to reinjure (the shoulder) remains to be
seen. Eventually we will have to do something about the shoulder.''
</P>
<P>
   It's unusual for a draft pick to sign only a one-year contract.
Both sides realized they couldn't agree on a multiyear deal because
of Hardy's injury.
</P>
<P>
   ``We didn't want a one-year deal,'' said Hardy's agent,  &UR; Ivory
Chandler. ``We were going back and forth on a two-year deal, and
then I left it totally up to Terry. He felt at this time this was
the best thing to do.''
</P>
<P>
   Terms were not disclosed, but those close to the negotiations
said Hardy received a smaller signing bonus because of the contract
being for only one year.
</P>
<P>
   Hardy isn't disappointed that he signed only a one-year deal and
will have to reopen negotiations next year.
</P>
<P>
   ``I feel blessed just to be part of this, participating in an
NFL camp,'' he said. ``I feel bad about standing around last week,
not working. I need to get in shape. I feel I have a chance to
contribute.'' &QL; 
Seeing the world
</P>
<P>
   Hayes, a 1996 seventh-round draft pick of the Cardinals, was
supposed to play in the World League last year for Barcelona, but
the team sent him home because he suffered a left foot injury.
</P>
<P>
   He was healthy in time for training camp but was released by the
Cardinals in late August.
</P>
<P>
   He joined the Amsterdam Admirals of the Europe League in the
spring and was used primarily as a blocking tight end. He had five
catches for 49 yards.
</P>
<P>
   ``I feel I've gotten better,'' he said. ``I improved as a
blocker and a receiver. I needed experience and playing time and
got both.''
</P>
<P>
   He also saw enough of the Dutch lifestyle to know it isn't for
him. Prostitution is legal and pornography is widespread.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's a very wild place,'' he said. ``You have to watch
yourself and keep yourself out of trouble.'' &QL; 
Short shots
</P>
<P>
   Former Oregon defensive tackle  &UR; Desmond Byrd (6-3, 300) signed
Monday after a tryout earlier in the day.
</P>
<P>
   Because of a scheduling conflict, wide receiver  &UR; Rob
 &UR; Moore will replace  &UR; Frank Sanders at Saturday's Minicamp for Kids.
The free clinic will be held from 9 a.m. until noon at the team's
Tempe training complex. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-06-16-98 1126EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
