Asparagus clafoutis; with recipe.
</P>
<P>
   SIMPLE-COOKING (Undated) _ The Minimalist: Beet rosti; with
recipe. By Mark Bittman.
</P>
<P>
   WINETALK (Undated) _ Don't give up on Bordeaux. Prices are going
through the roof and in recent weeks there has been some
unpleasantness at one of the chateaus, Giscours, over alleged
shortcuts in the winemaking. But keep in mind that there are two
Bordeaux. By Frank J. Prial.
</P>
<P>
   WINE-TASTINGS (Undated) _ Wine of the week: Planeta La Segreta
Rosso 1996, Sicily. About $15. By Frank J. Prial.
</P>
<P>
   EATING-WELL (Undated) _ So you think your hamburger is safely
cooked when it is brown all the way through? Forget it. Hamburger
meat turns brown for reasons that have nothing to do with cooking,
according to tests done by the federal government. And that means
it can hold bacteria that make you sick. By Marian Burros.
</P>
