<SLUG> BC-TRIVIA-Q&AMP;A-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
YAHTZEE WAS INDEED INVENTED ON A YACHT
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By ROGERS CADENHEAD 
c.1998 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Q: My brother-in-law told me that Yahtzee got its name from a
yacht. Is this true?
</P>
<P>
   _ A.G., Burleson, Texas
</P>
<P>
   A: The dice game Yahtzee was invented by a Canadian couple in
1956 and was often played with guests on their yacht.
</P>
<P>
   The couple approached toy manufacturer Edwin S. Lowe in the
hopes he would print a few copies of their ``yacht game'' as gifts,
according to the World Wide Web site Toy Tips, at www.toytips.com.
</P>
<P>
   Impressed with the game, Lowe bought all rights from the couple,
who agreed to sell it for a few copies of the game and no
royalties. He renamed it Yahtzee.
</P>
<P>
   Q: I received a Silver Star during World War II. I know that the
Congressional Medal of Honor is No. 1. What place does the Silver
Star have?
</P>
<P>
   _ U.K., Cleburne, Texas
</P>
<P>
   A: The Silver Star is the fifth highest medal awarded by the
United States Army, said Carol Bush, a military personnel
technician with Army Reserve Personnel Command.
</P>
<P>
   It ranks behind the Congressional Medal of Honor, Distinguished
Service Cross, Defense Distinguished Service and Distinguished
Service Medal.
</P>
<P>
   Other branches of military service have similar orders of
precedence:
</P>
<P>
   Marine Corps and Navy: Congressional Medal of Honor, Navy Cross,
Defense Distinguished Service, Navy Distinguished Service, Silver
Star.
</P>
<P>
   Air Force: Congressional Medal of Honor, Air Force Cross,
Defense Distinguished Service, Air Force Distinguished Service,
Silver Star.
</P>
<P>
   Coast Guard: Congressional Medal of Honor, Navy Cross, Defense
Distinguished Service, Coast Guard Distinguished Service, Silver
Star.
</P>
<P>
   Q: What year did the city of Houston reach 1 million population?
</P>
<P>
   _ P.B., Granbury, Texas
</P>
<P>
   A: According to the ``Lone Star Book of Texas Records,'' with
the 1970 census, Houston officially became the first Texas city
with 1 million inhabitants.
</P>
<P>
   Its population in that census was 1.23 million. By comparison,
Fort Worth had 393,000 residents and Dallas 844,000.
</P>
<P>
   The first city in world history to reach 1 million was London in
1811, according to ``The First of Everything'' by Dennis Sanders.
</P>
<P>
   (Rogers Cadenhead writes a trivia column for the Fort Worth
Star-Telegram. He can be reached at the Star-Telegram, Box 1870,
Fort Worth, Texas 76101; or by E-mail at trivia(at)prefect.com.
Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide Web:
www.star-telegram.com)
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
