</P>
<P>
   GOLF-TECH _ As questions continue to circulate about the USGA's
possible ban on high-tech equipment like oversized titanium
drivers, extra-long putters and far-flying golf balls, the USGA may
make an announcement at this week's U.S. Open. While some speculate
they'll only require a uniform ball and leave the rest alone,
there's also a possiblility that any event that uses the USGA's
``Rules of Golf'' will be banned from using several kinds of
high-tech equipment. (Sheeley, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) ETA 8
p.m. ET.
</P>
<P>
   BOHLS-COLUMN-TWO _ AUSTIN _ Mike Campbell was about to make his
biggest comeback, perhaps his best contribution, if two decades too
late. Unfortunately, life is playing one of its cruelest tricks on
this most honorable of men. At a time when new UT head fooball
coach Mack Brown and defensive coordinator Carl Reese were
petitioning him to share the brilliance that was Campbell's
defensive intellect, he is lying critically ill in a hospital bed
at Seton Medical Center, a victim of lymphoma. (Bohls, Austin
American-Statesman) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
