<HEADLINE>
&HT;    
 &HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    N.Y. Times dons leisure Web suit
 &HT;    By Frances Katz
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   The online battle for the leisure time of New Yorkers heated up
a notch Tuesday when The New York Times launched New York Today
(http://www.nytoday.com), a guide to arts, entertainment and
leisure activities in the Big Apple. Martin Nisenholtz, president
of the New York Times Electronic Media Co., said in a statement
that the Web site will include a searchable database of information
along with editorial content and full Yellow Pages for New York,
New Jersey and Connecticut.
</P>
<P>
   Although NYToday enters the city guide arena with The New York
Times name behind it and a laundry list of 300 advertisers, it
still faces an uphill battle for users in the very crowded New York
City guide arena. Microsoft Sidewalk, America Online's Digital
City, Yahoo! and Citysearch already are competing for the attention
of time-crunched New York Web surfers. There are also restaurant
and travel guides devoted to New York. But the Times is confident
there's room for everybody. ``In the future,'' Nisenholtz said,
``we expect thousands of groups from all over the city to take
advantage of this free and unique offering.''
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
