<P>
   WOODWARD-DECISION (Boston) -- Massachusetts' top court rules
narrowly that Judge Hiller Zobel acted within his discretion when
he reduced the jury's verdict from second-degree murder to
manslaughter in the Louise Woodward case. By Anne E. Kornblut. 1500
words. (a and i coding)
</P>
<P>
   w/
</P>
<P>
   WOODWARD-ANALYSIS (Boston) -- The decision is a mixed assessment
of Judge Hiller Zobel. The justices say he erred in not allowing
the jury to consider manslaughter, but then corrected his own error
in reducing the verdict. By David Armstrong. 1200 words. (a and i
coding)
</P>
<P>
   w/
