<HEADLINE>
CLINTONS SET RETURN TO VINEYARD 
</HEADLINE>
  
 (w and a coding)   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By ANN SCALES  
 c.1998 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON _ President Clinton is set to return to Martha's
Vineyard for a vacation of about two weeks in August, while his
wife and daughter may spend the entire month on the island, White
House sources said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   The president is expected to arrive the weekend of Aug. 15,
joining Hillary Rodham Clinton and Chelsea.
</P>
<P>
   The Clintons are expected to stay at their usual perch _ the
sprawling Edgartown home of Boston businessman Richard Friedman.
``The Clinton family are always welcome at my family's house,''
said Friedman, who otherwise declined comment.
</P>
<P>
   White House officials said the Clintons' vacation plans are
still not finalized.
</P>
<P>
   This would be the Clintons' fourth Vineyard vacation. The family
spent the first two presidential vacations on the island, and then
stayed away two summers, opting for Jackson Hole, Wyo., and the
Grand Tetons.
</P>
<P>
   They returned to Martha's Vineyard last year for the longest
vacation of the Clinton presidency _ a full three weeks. They spent
their vacation socializing with celebrities, walking along the
beach, reading, playing board games, listening to '60s music, and,
in the case of the first duffer, golfing and jogging.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
