<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-GLF-USOPEN-MARTIN-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
MARTIN IS CLEARED TO USE GOLF CART 
</HEADLINE>
   (See also GLF-USOPEN) 
 (ja) 
 By CLIFTON BROWN    
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service  
<TEXT>
<P>
   SAN FRANCISCO _ The U.S. Golf Association will allow Casey
Martin to use a regular golf cart this week at the U.S. Open.
</P>
<P>
   The decision was made Tuesday after Martin continued to have
mechanical and handling difficulties with his specially designed
one-seat cart.
</P>
<P>
   On holes where Martin is not able to drive close to the greens,
a marshal will drive Martin's cart to the next tee.
</P>
<P>
   Martin, who uses a regular cart in Nike Tour events, was
relieved by the decision.
</P>
<P>
   ``I think the single cart ride is a great idea; I just don't
think it's quite there yet,'' said Martin, who had a single-seat
cart stall on him Monday. ``It's got a few kinks that make it
difficult to drive, especially when there are 37,000 people. I'm
excited that they gave me a regular cart because it will make my
time at the Open easier.''
</P>
<P>
   Martin, who is afflicted with a circulatory disorder in his
right leg, also announced that he has accepted a sponsor's
exemption to play at the Canon Greater Hartford Open next month. It
will be Martin's first PGA Tour event since he successfully sued
the tour for the right to use a cart earlier this year.
</P>
<P>
   A large gallery followed the threesome of Martin, Tiger Woods
and Joel Kribel during Tuesday's practice round at the Olympic
Club, and the crowd was clearly supportive of Martin.
</P>
<P>
   ``It has been a great experience,'' he said. ``For the last six
months, my life has changed quite a bit. Coming up the 18th hole,
there must have been 15,000 people. This is the stuff I dreamt
about 10 years ago.''
</P>
<P>
   Martin won a friendly skins game with Woods during their round.
``He has yet to pay me,'' Martin said.
</P>
<P>
   While many players still believe a cart should not be allowed in
competition, Martin said his peers had received him warmly.
</P>
<P>
   ``I have seen a few players that were outspoken,'' Martin said.
``I am not going to name names. They didn't go out of there way to
say hi, but at the same time, they didn't sneer at me either. I'm
not getting caught up in who said what. I'm enjoying the
experience.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-06-16-98 2234EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
