<HEADLINE>
HOW SENATE VOTED ON LAWYERS' FEES 
</HEADLINE>
  (With TOBACCO-CONGRESS) 
(pr) 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON _ Following is the 49-48 roll-call vote by which the
Senate voted Tuesday to limit lawyers' fees in lawsuits against
cigarette makers in an amendment to tobacco legislation sponsored
by Sen. Slade Gorton, R-Wash. Forty-five Republicans and four
Democrats voted yes. Forty Democrats and eight Republicans voted
no. One Democrat and one Republican voted ``present'' and one
Republican was absent.
