   (NYT13) UNDATED -- June 16, 1998 -- BARNEYS-RESIGN, 6-16 -- Bob
Pressman, left, and his brother, Gene, the grandsons of the founder
of Barney's Inc., the luxury fashion retailer, will step down as
co-chief executives as early as this week as part of the company's
plan to emerge from bankruptcy. The two joined Barney's in the
1970s and eventually put stores everywhere from Beverly Hills to
Asia. (Fred R. Conrad/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT12) HICKSVILLE, N.Y. -- June 16, 1998 -- NY-LILCO-SEVERANCE,
6-16 -- Dr. William Catacosinos, former chairman of the Long Island
Lighting Co., now chairman of Marketspan, in his office.
Marketspan, the product of a merger between Lilco and Brooklyn
Union Gas, supplies the electricity, management and workforce to
operate the old Lilco system. A week after the takeover, the power
authority disclosed that Lilco had made secret payments to 26
executives. Catacosinos, the prime beneficiary, received $42
million. (Vic DeLucia/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
