Paul Soros, 71, the older brother of George, the 67-year-old
financier-philanthropist famous for giving away nearly $2 billion.
Last month Paul Soros and his wife, Daisy, made their first foray
into major philanthropy when they announced the establishment of a
$50 million trust to help underwrite American graduate education
for immigrants and their children. (Librado Romero/New York Times
Photo)
